Write an SQL query to find the employee with the 7th highest salary.
Write an SQL query to find all employees who do not have a manager. (Assume Employee and Manager are two different tables.)
Write an SQL query to find all managers who do not have any employees reporting to them.
Write an SQL query to find employees whose salary is greater than their manager’s salary and their manager’s manager’s salary.

SELECT emp_name FROM employees
WHERE salary = (
    SELECT DISTINCT salary
    FROM employees
    ORDER BY salary DESC
    LIMIT 6, 1
);

SELECT e.emp_id, e.emp_name
FROM employees e
INNER JOIN managers m
    ON e.manager_id = m.manager_id
WHERE e.manager_id IS NULL;



